1
00:01:53,020 --> 00:01:54,440
Sixteen!

2
00:01:55,990 --> 00:01:58,530
Hey! He's still standing!

3
00:02:01,620 --> 00:02:03,540
Seventeen!

4
00:02:04,370 --> 00:02:05,540
Eighteen!

5
00:02:08,790 --> 00:02:10,380
Nineteen!

6
00:02:18,340 --> 00:02:21,090
Twenty!

7
00:02:22,930 --> 00:02:25,010
I lost!

8
00:02:25,770 --> 00:02:28,600
He's amazing even though he's so tiny!

9
00:02:29,980 --> 00:02:31,980
He's still standing!

10
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:34,650
That's impressive!

11
00:02:34,730 --> 00:02:38,360
I lost big money because of you, Drott!

12
00:02:38,860 --> 00:02:41,030
What are you doing!

13
00:02:41,110 --> 00:02:43,780
Hurry up and crack his head open!

14
00:02:43,870 --> 00:02:45,540
Keep your eyes on him!

15
00:02:45,620 --> 00:02:47,000
Damn it!

16
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:48,370
<i>Something is not right.</i>

17
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:51,830
<i>My punches feel light for some reason.</i>

18
00:02:52,630 --> 00:02:55,920
Damn it!

19
00:02:56,750 --> 00:02:57,960
<i>Interesting…</i>

20
00:02:58,460 --> 00:03:01,680
<i>That messenger is indeed</i>
<i>used to being punched.</i>

21
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:05,890
<i>Right before he's hit by the fist,</i>
<i>he twists his neck and hips</i>

22
00:03:06,390 --> 00:03:08,680
<i>to distribute the impact</i>
<i>throughout his body.</i>

23
00:03:11,230 --> 00:03:12,980
<i>But it's so subtle that nobody</i>

24
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:16,320
<i>realizes that he is dodging the attack.</i>

25
00:03:18,190 --> 00:03:20,400
<i>However, Drott is also a skilled fighter.</i>

26
00:03:21,320 --> 00:03:23,740
<i>He won't last very long at this rate.</i>

27
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:27,410
Twenty-three!

28
00:03:29,160 --> 00:03:31,790
Twenty-four!

29
00:03:32,290 --> 00:03:33,460
Thorfinn…

30
00:03:36,170 --> 00:03:37,500
<i>Even still…</i>

31
00:03:38,130 --> 00:03:41,260
<i>violence should be the last resort.</i>

32
00:03:43,010 --> 00:03:44,180
<i>I wish…</i>

33
00:03:45,180 --> 00:03:49,140
<i>I wish I knew how to choose</i>
<i>the first course of action that's best.</i>

34
00:03:51,480 --> 00:03:54,270
<i>Is this it?</i>

35
00:03:55,230 --> 00:03:57,900
<i>This is the "first course of action"?</i>

36
00:03:59,780 --> 00:04:02,990
<i>Not punching back</i>
<i>and just enduring it all?</i>

37
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,990
<i>Is that how</i>

38
00:04:07,410 --> 00:04:10,870
<i>you are going to live from now on?</i>

39
00:04:16,210 --> 00:04:18,170
What are you going to do?

40
00:04:18,250 --> 00:04:19,590
All right!

41
00:04:26,470 --> 00:04:29,140
What's that? Are they fighting?

42
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:32,600
Hey…

43
00:04:33,100 --> 00:04:34,640
Come on, Drott!

44
00:04:35,810 --> 00:04:37,020
Thorfinn!

45
00:04:38,690 --> 00:04:40,280
Stop it!

46
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:41,650
What's going on?

47
00:04:43,150 --> 00:04:46,240
He has nothing to do with this farm!

48
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:49,490
<i>Oh no!</i>

49
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:10,640
All right! I felt that one!

50
00:05:11,140 --> 00:05:14,180
Thirty-two!

51
00:05:14,270 --> 00:05:16,810
That made a crazy sound!

52
00:05:17,980 --> 00:05:19,190
Did he die?

53
00:05:21,110 --> 00:05:22,320
Thorfinn!

54
00:05:30,410 --> 00:05:31,830
What's going on?

55
00:05:31,910 --> 00:05:34,200
I thought you guys left the farm already.

56
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:37,040
How did it turn into this?

57
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:42,880
If he endures 100 strikes from them,

58
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:46,720
they will let him speak
directly with the king.

59
00:05:47,470 --> 00:05:50,300
That's what they promised.

60
00:05:52,390 --> 00:05:53,560
No way…

61
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:56,890
He did it for the farm?

62
00:06:02,570 --> 00:06:05,440
That's enough. Stop this.

63
00:06:06,150 --> 00:06:09,950
The farm is surrendering.
They've decided already.

64
00:06:11,870 --> 00:06:13,410
You idiot.

65
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:17,870
You're too nice for your own good.

66
00:06:18,750 --> 00:06:21,040
If a conversation could've solved this,

67
00:06:21,130 --> 00:06:22,840
we would've done that already.

68
00:06:27,380 --> 00:06:30,340
Are you sure about that?

69
00:06:34,350 --> 00:06:35,850
Did you really,

70
00:06:37,390 --> 00:06:39,060
earnestly,

71
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:43,560
put in the effort to solve this

72
00:06:45,570 --> 00:06:47,070
over a conversation?

73
00:06:51,910 --> 00:06:54,280
Just because they took up their swords,

74
00:06:55,490 --> 00:06:57,290
you retaliated with your sword

75
00:06:58,080 --> 00:07:00,870
without even thinking about it.

76
00:07:01,960 --> 00:07:03,920
That was 32 punches.

77
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,880
-Let's divide the money.
-He got up!

78
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:07,130
Hey, wait a second.

79
00:07:08,670 --> 00:07:10,220
You must be kidding!

80
00:07:10,300 --> 00:07:11,130
No way!

81
00:07:11,220 --> 00:07:14,140
He stood up!

82
00:07:20,690 --> 00:07:24,190
What are you relaxing for,
you middle-parted jerk!

83
00:07:25,610 --> 00:07:29,570
Your punches are nothing more
than a bug bite to me.

84
00:07:30,650 --> 00:07:32,530
You have 68 more punches.

85
00:07:33,030 --> 00:07:34,740
Hurry up and get it over with.

86
00:07:35,410 --> 00:07:37,330
I don't have all day.

87
00:07:38,830 --> 00:07:41,750
I have people waiting for me!

88
00:07:55,090 --> 00:07:57,560
Stop it! This battle is--

89
00:08:00,060 --> 00:08:03,100
Einar, he'll die if he continues.

90
00:08:41,850 --> 00:08:45,060
Ninety-eight.

91
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:53,030
Ninety-nine.

92
00:08:59,620 --> 00:09:00,950
A Hundred.

93
00:09:30,730 --> 00:09:33,360
Thorfinn, son of Thors.

94
00:09:35,990 --> 00:09:37,860
I'm sorry I doubted you.

95
00:09:39,570 --> 00:09:40,780
You are…

96
00:09:42,410 --> 00:09:45,790
You are a real warrior.

97
00:09:52,670 --> 00:09:53,880
Captain,

98
00:09:55,090 --> 00:09:57,840
this man once served the king

99
00:09:57,930 --> 00:10:00,300
as a royal guard, just like us.

100
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:05,310
Please grant Thorfinn
a meeting with the king.

101
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:18,860
You're small, but it seems
you are well trained, Thorfinn.

102
00:10:20,030 --> 00:10:23,330
But why didn't you punch back?

103
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:25,700
If you defeated Drott,

104
00:10:25,790 --> 00:10:30,080
that would have proved
your skill as a former royal guard.

105
00:10:32,590 --> 00:10:35,050
What kind of question is that?

106
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:39,680
There's no point in a peace negotiation
if you go around punching people.

107
00:10:41,010 --> 00:10:44,680
I met you guys for the first time today.

108
00:10:45,180 --> 00:10:48,480
We don't know anything about each other.

109
00:10:48,980 --> 00:10:50,810
We hold no grudges.

110
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:54,690
So why do we have to fight each other?

111
00:10:54,770 --> 00:10:55,610
It's ridiculous.

112
00:10:56,940 --> 00:11:00,280
Canute and Ketil
are the ones who want to fight.

113
00:11:00,780 --> 00:11:03,490
The two leaders should just
play a game of <i>hnefatafl</i>

114
00:11:03,570 --> 00:11:05,740
and settle their issues.

115
00:11:06,410 --> 00:11:08,250
There is absolutely no reason

116
00:11:08,750 --> 00:11:11,330
for all these people to gather
and shed blood.

117
00:11:16,340 --> 00:11:19,550
We met for the first time today.

118
00:11:21,430 --> 00:11:23,930
You guys are not my enemies.

119
00:11:38,070 --> 00:11:40,820
No one is my enemy.

120
00:11:50,410 --> 00:11:52,460
You sure have guts

121
00:11:53,210 --> 00:11:56,040
to boldly deny war in front of

122
00:11:56,130 --> 00:11:58,840
this many professional warriors.

123
00:12:00,130 --> 00:12:01,550
But to think…

124
00:12:03,340 --> 00:12:06,010
Ketil and His Majesty
playing <i>hnefatafl</i>, huh?

125
00:12:07,180 --> 00:12:08,600
What's so funny?

126
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:10,180
Pardon me.

127
00:12:10,680 --> 00:12:14,900
Try proposing that idea
to the king himself.

128
00:12:16,310 --> 00:12:17,770
His Majesty

129
00:12:17,860 --> 00:12:20,730
is not fighting wars because he wants to.

130
00:12:21,570 --> 00:12:24,110
If you are allowed to speak with him,

131
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:25,910
you will come to see his intentions.

132
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:32,080
Make way.

133
00:12:32,160 --> 00:12:35,080
I will take this messenger to the king.

134
00:12:44,760 --> 00:12:46,930
Come on, Einar.

135
00:12:49,510 --> 00:12:52,560
We're going to meet
the very person who starts wars.

136
00:12:53,640 --> 00:12:55,770
I'm sure you have something to say.

137
00:12:57,770 --> 00:12:59,270
Yeah!

138
00:12:59,770 --> 00:13:02,780
I have a whole lot to say.

139
00:13:41,020 --> 00:13:42,230
All of them

140
00:13:43,150 --> 00:13:45,360
were killed in this battle?

141
00:13:46,900 --> 00:13:48,860
Don't look, Einar.

142
00:13:50,780 --> 00:13:51,950
Pater…

143
00:13:52,870 --> 00:13:54,120
Don't look.

144
00:13:54,910 --> 00:13:57,830
If you find Pater among them,

145
00:13:58,330 --> 00:14:00,080
you'll become too emotional.

146
00:14:33,490 --> 00:14:35,450
All right, let him through.

147
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:38,460
I'll respect your decision.

148
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:40,330
Thank you very much.

149
00:14:42,080 --> 00:14:44,170
You may come forward!

150
00:15:14,530 --> 00:15:16,040
So you were alive?

151
00:15:17,870 --> 00:15:19,000
It's been a while,

152
00:15:19,830 --> 00:15:20,660
Thorfinn.

153
00:15:23,880 --> 00:15:25,000
After I

154
00:15:25,670 --> 00:15:27,670
turned you into a slave…

155
00:15:29,760 --> 00:15:30,590
Or rather,

156
00:15:31,630 --> 00:15:33,220
after what I did to Askeladd,

157
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:36,140
you must really hate me.

158
00:15:41,850 --> 00:15:44,650
I took up a weapon against
the royal family of Denmark

159
00:15:45,150 --> 00:15:47,190
and yet my life was spared.

160
00:15:48,530 --> 00:15:51,700
I am grateful for your consideration.

161
00:15:53,780 --> 00:15:54,910
I am sorry

162
00:15:55,910 --> 00:15:57,620
about the cut on your face.

163
00:15:58,910 --> 00:16:01,500
<i>The man who left a scar</i>
<i>on the king's face…</i>

164
00:16:02,580 --> 00:16:04,540
<i>Thorfinn Karlsefni.</i>

165
00:16:05,670 --> 00:16:09,420
<i>He was said to have fought</i>
<i>on par with Thorkell.</i>

166
00:16:10,460 --> 00:16:12,720
<i>Who knew he was so small and young.</i>

167
00:16:14,430 --> 00:16:16,930
You cut the king?

168
00:16:19,640 --> 00:16:22,940
I can't recognize you
with your face looking like that,

169
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:26,020
but it seems you really are
the Thorfinn I know.

170
00:16:27,150 --> 00:16:28,190
I must say,

171
00:16:28,770 --> 00:16:31,150
you really learned
how to give a model answer.

172
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:36,160
<i>Four years, huh?</i>

173
00:16:38,410 --> 00:16:41,910
<i>It has already been four years since then.</i>

174
00:16:43,500 --> 00:16:45,210
That is enough time

175
00:16:45,870 --> 00:16:47,630
to change a person.

176
00:16:55,930 --> 00:16:59,050
Canute, please leave this farm alone.

177
00:17:00,180 --> 00:17:01,270
I can't.

178
00:17:02,980 --> 00:17:05,270
This all started because of Ketil.

179
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:10,480
Ketil's son Olmar held a grudge
because he couldn't become a thegn

180
00:17:10,570 --> 00:17:13,570
and murdered ten of my men.

181
00:17:15,110 --> 00:17:16,240
I heard about that.

182
00:17:16,910 --> 00:17:18,700
But you've done enough.

183
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:21,950
More than 100 people
from the farm's side died.

184
00:17:22,700 --> 00:17:24,750
With this many workers dead,

185
00:17:25,250 --> 00:17:28,040
this area may not be able
to get back on its feet.

186
00:17:30,130 --> 00:17:33,050
I summoned them to surrender beforehand.

187
00:17:33,630 --> 00:17:37,090
It is Ketil's fault for misjudging
the difference in our strength.

188
00:17:38,010 --> 00:17:39,090
And that is why

189
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:42,850
this battle will not end
until the Ketil family is dealt with.

190
00:17:44,930 --> 00:17:46,390
More like,

191
00:17:46,480 --> 00:17:48,600
until you make this farm your own.

192
00:17:51,190 --> 00:17:53,480
Your pretense isn't fooling anyone.

193
00:17:53,980 --> 00:17:57,860
You call yourself a king,
but you're nothing but a robber.

194
00:17:58,570 --> 00:18:01,120
What makes you different from

195
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:03,790
any other Viking gang lord out there?

196
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:07,460
<i>If you want a field that bad,</i>

197
00:18:07,540 --> 00:18:09,250
<i>try making it yourself.</i>

198
00:18:10,290 --> 00:18:13,090
<i>Plow the soil, watch over it,</i>

199
00:18:13,170 --> 00:18:14,670
<i>and cultivate it yourself!</i>

200
00:18:15,170 --> 00:18:16,510
<i>Then</i>

201
00:18:17,010 --> 00:18:21,010
you will really understand
how horrible it is

202
00:18:22,140 --> 00:18:24,180
to take it away.

203
00:18:28,350 --> 00:18:29,390
Canute,

204
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:34,070
<i>remember you told me back in Gainsborough,</i>

205
00:18:35,900 --> 00:18:38,200
<i>that you will make a paradise on earth,</i>

206
00:18:39,030 --> 00:18:42,200
<i>a utopia for those who are suffering?</i>

207
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:48,160
Is that still your wish?

208
00:18:51,750 --> 00:18:53,090
A gang lord, huh?

209
00:18:54,040 --> 00:18:55,500
Indeed,

210
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:59,470
I am the Viking gang lord
of all Viking gang lords.

211
00:19:02,340 --> 00:19:04,260
I am the emperor.

212
00:19:04,760 --> 00:19:07,560
The strongest Viking of the North Sea.

213
00:19:08,930 --> 00:19:12,440
The ruler of the largest territory
in the Nordic region.

214
00:19:12,940 --> 00:19:14,900
The commander

215
00:19:14,980 --> 00:19:17,610
of thousands of ships
and tens of thousands of soldiers.

216
00:19:17,690 --> 00:19:20,200
My power exceeds human understanding

217
00:19:20,700 --> 00:19:22,490
and makes the impossible possible.

218
00:19:26,620 --> 00:19:27,580
Look!

219
00:19:28,580 --> 00:19:31,620
I will calm those waves with my power.

220
00:19:35,670 --> 00:19:37,880
In the name of Canute, the emperor,

221
00:19:38,380 --> 00:19:41,090
I order the waves to calm down!

222
00:19:59,110 --> 00:20:03,070
Did you see my power?

223
00:20:04,740 --> 00:20:07,870
I cannot even stop the rippling waves.

224
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:12,540
Do you know who is making

225
00:20:12,620 --> 00:20:13,710
those waves?

226
00:20:21,760 --> 00:20:22,800
It's God.

227
00:20:24,590 --> 00:20:27,550
<i>Creating a paradise on earth</i>

228
00:20:28,060 --> 00:20:31,350
<i>means going against the rules he has set.</i>

229
00:20:32,180 --> 00:20:34,480
<i>It's a rebellion against God.</i>

230
00:20:36,310 --> 00:20:38,690
As long as we abide by his rules,

231
00:20:39,190 --> 00:20:41,320
humans cannot find happiness.

232
00:20:43,900 --> 00:20:45,240
Rebellion?

233
00:20:45,820 --> 00:20:48,120
Look at us, Thorfinn.

234
00:20:49,410 --> 00:20:51,250
Look at us, Vikings.

235
00:20:52,410 --> 00:20:55,080
We are the bearers
of chaos and destruction,

236
00:20:55,580 --> 00:20:57,540
the plunderers of terror.

237
00:20:58,340 --> 00:21:02,630
Do you think we have the right
to live in paradise?

238
00:21:03,840 --> 00:21:07,260
<i>But that is exactly what humans are.</i>

239
00:21:08,180 --> 00:21:09,680
<i>We encompass</i>

240
00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:13,270
<i>the very essence of sinning,</i>
<i>wandering humans.</i>

241
00:21:15,230 --> 00:21:18,360
I must save these people
who were abandoned by God,

242
00:21:18,860 --> 00:21:21,820
or else building a paradise
will be impossible.

243
00:21:24,570 --> 00:21:27,410
Saving the Vikings?

244
00:21:28,530 --> 00:21:29,620
That's right.

245
00:21:30,740 --> 00:21:33,160
Subjugating them, controlling them,

246
00:21:33,750 --> 00:21:35,410
unifying their power,

247
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:39,080
and leading them to paradise is something

248
00:21:39,170 --> 00:21:41,420
only I can do.

249
00:21:42,380 --> 00:21:44,130
I need power.

250
00:21:45,550 --> 00:21:47,510
I will unify the power of humans

251
00:21:49,010 --> 00:21:51,930
<i>and fight against God.</i>

252
00:21:59,060 --> 00:22:01,820
<i>You're an incredible man, Canute.</i>

253
00:22:02,940 --> 00:22:05,110
<i>I've never even thought about</i>

254
00:22:05,610 --> 00:22:07,570
<i>saving the Vikings.</i>

255
00:22:09,820 --> 00:22:12,200
I am going to smack you.

256
00:22:12,950 --> 00:22:15,250
I don't give a damn about whatever

257
00:22:15,330 --> 00:22:16,710
big plans you have in mind.

258
00:22:17,330 --> 00:22:21,170
But if you are going to kill
people today just for that,

259
00:22:21,250 --> 00:22:22,960
who is going to save them?

260
00:22:23,670 --> 00:22:26,340
You save Vikings
because they give you power,

261
00:22:26,420 --> 00:22:28,380
but you kill and rob from people

262
00:22:28,470 --> 00:22:29,930
who are useless to you?

263
00:22:30,430 --> 00:22:33,760
Building paradise? Don't make me laugh!

264
00:22:35,810 --> 00:22:36,810
I had

265
00:22:37,520 --> 00:22:39,770
my village burned down by King Ethelred

266
00:22:40,270 --> 00:22:42,810
and my family killed by King Sweyn.

267
00:22:43,860 --> 00:22:47,440
I don't care what kind of ideals they had.

268
00:22:49,530 --> 00:22:51,200
I've had enough!

269
00:22:51,700 --> 00:22:55,790
I will not be a victim
to you people anymore.

270
00:23:02,920 --> 00:23:04,380
Hate me if you want.

271
00:23:05,130 --> 00:23:07,630
I don't need your forgiveness.

272
00:23:09,010 --> 00:23:10,630
What did you say?

273
00:23:12,800 --> 00:23:14,100
Stop it, Einar.

274
00:23:19,350 --> 00:23:21,770
Canute, let me ask you again.

275
00:23:22,520 --> 00:23:24,900
Do you have any intention
of leaving this farm?

276
00:23:25,520 --> 00:23:29,650
No. I need Ketil's wealth for my project.

277
00:23:32,740 --> 00:23:35,120
So what will you do, Thorfinn?

278
00:23:35,620 --> 00:23:38,750
Will you kill me right here, right now?

279
00:23:41,500 --> 00:23:43,460
If you don't kill me,

280
00:23:43,960 --> 00:23:46,170
there is no way to stop me.

281
00:25:53,340 --> 00:25:54,840
<i>"Two paths."</i>

282
00:25:54,920 --> 00:25:57,010
Subtitle translation by: Kiko Morita

